//Write an if statement that tests to see whether a String stored in a variable named phrase begins with a capital letter. 
//If the string begins with a capital letter, print capital . If not, print not capital . 
//Use at least one method call from the Character class in your solution. 

//1. Character.isUpperCase(char ch) java method determines if the specified character is an uppercase character.
if (Character.isUpperCase(phrase.charAt(0))){
    System.out.println("capital");
}else{
    System.out.println("not capital");
}

test #1:hello
output: not capital

test #2:How are you
output: capital

test #3:Mississippi
output:capital

test #4:peanut butter
output:not capital


/*2. 
Character class isUpperCase() method
isUpperCase() method is available in java.lang package.
isUpperCase() method is used to check whether the given char value is uppercase or not. ex: String.isUpperCase("w")
isUpperCase() method does not throw an exception at the time of checking the given char value is uppercase or not.
//boolean syntex
*/

public class IsUpperCaseOfCharacterClass {
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
        boolean result1 = Character.isUpperCase('P'); 
        boolean result2 = Character.isUpperCase('p');

        System.out.println("Character.isUpperCase('P'): " + result1);
        System.out.println("Character.isUpperCase('p'): " + result2);
    }
}

output: 
Character.isUpperCase('P'): true
Character.isUpperCase('p'): false
